1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,600
When you first leaf through the series,

2
00:00:02,060 --> 00:00:04,480
the premise looks simple, even repetitive.

3
00:00:04,940 --> 00:00:07,680
Into one ordinary moment after another — a

4
00:00:07,680 --> 00:00:09,900
throne room, a study, a day in the

5
00:00:09,900 --> 00:00:12,440
fields — strides the same uninvited guest:

6
00:00:12,860 --> 00:00:13,400
a skeleton.

7
00:00:13,840 --> 00:00:15,660
Death has come, and Death always wins.

8
00:00:16,080 --> 00:00:17,680
But look at how he behaves, and the

9
00:00:17,680 --> 00:00:18,960
simplicity falls away.

10
00:00:19,460 --> 00:00:21,460
Holbein's Death is not a solemn, hooded

11
00:00:21,460 --> 00:00:22,180
reaper.

12
00:00:22,480 --> 00:00:24,580
He is a performer, and the joke is

13
00:00:24,580 --> 00:00:26,140
always tailored to his victim.

14
00:00:26,140 --> 00:00:28,840
He turns into a kind of dispenser of

15
00:00:28,840 --> 00:00:31,520
justice — denouncing greed and the abuse

16
00:00:31,520 --> 00:00:32,080
of power.

17
00:00:32,600 --> 00:00:34,240
He robs the rich man of his money

18
00:00:34,240 --> 00:00:35,520
before he takes his soul.

19
00:00:35,860 --> 00:00:38,320
He boldly hauls an abbot away by his

20
00:00:38,320 --> 00:00:38,800
vestments.

21
00:00:39,020 --> 00:00:39,940
He skewers a knight.

22
00:00:40,200 --> 00:00:42,240
For the nobility, Death arrives as an

23
00:00:42,240 --> 00:00:44,640
opponent who simply cannot be beaten.

24
00:00:45,100 --> 00:00:47,180
In one scene after another, he doesn't

25
00:00:47,180 --> 00:00:49,640
merely take the powerful — he mocks the

26
00:00:49,640 --> 00:00:51,920
very thing they lived for, and more often

27
00:00:51,920 --> 00:00:53,960
than not he holds up an hourglass to

28
00:00:53,960 --> 00:00:54,380
do it.

29
00:00:55,180 --> 00:00:57,360
That little glass runs through the series

30
00:00:57,360 --> 00:00:58,160
like a refrain.

31
00:00:58,620 --> 00:01:00,840
And then he reaches the people who never

32
00:01:00,840 --> 00:01:03,220
had any power at all — and something

33
00:01:03,220 --> 00:01:05,160
strange happens to his manner.
